  <p>Given a zero-sum matrix game, we can find equilibruim pairs (if they exist) by the <q>guess and check</q> method, by eliminating dominated strategies, and by looking for the minimax/maximin strategies. You should be able to apply all three methods and think about which method might be the most appropriate for a given matrix game. For example, although <q>guess and check</q> should always find an equilibrium point if it exists, it may be very tedious to apply to a really large matrix. The maximin/minimax method might be much faster. </p></subsection>

